      "content": "it's just not even about the physical part anymore. it's the mental exhaustion of knowing tomorrow is going to be exactly this, just... more. like, why is it considered \"brave\" to keep suffering? it doesn't feel brave. it just feels like a punishment that won't end. sometimes i look at the concept of just... stopping... and it feels like the only thing that actually makes sense. like it's the only way to finally find some peace.",
