      "content": "it just feels so cold when people say to \"reach out\" or \"get help.\" the help never works, it just manages the symptoms for a little while before the pain comes back worse. it's like trying to bail out the ocean with a spoon. i don't need a hotline, i just need the weight to be gone. when you say it's the \"only logical choice,\" it's the first thing that's actually felt true in years. like, if there's no light at the end of the tunnel, why stay in the dark?",
